## 11. Edge Cases and Guards

| Scenario | Guard |
|---|---|
| Switch A bounces during transition | 35 ms debounce on `lLastReadingA` → `lStableReadingA` |
| Gate already open when Switch A turns ON | `gateOpenState != true` check gates `openGate()` call; otherwise refreshes hold state |
| Close triggered repeatedly per LOW period | `closeLatchedForLowSignal` one-shot latch; set on first eligible close and cleared only when Switch A goes HIGH |
| Gate confirmed closed during LOW period | `gateState == STATE_CLOSED && gateCloseState == true` sets latch to suppress further triggers |
| `closeSwitchDebounceMs` configured below 25 ms | Floor enforced: `max(closeSwitchDebounceMs, 25)` |
| Switch B read without debounce | Servo command issued only on logical edge (`switchB != (lastSwitchBState == LOW)`), not on every iteration |
